## 16. Network Isolation & Security

### Dark Mesh

- Custom Kademlia protocol: `/introvert/kad/1.0.0`
- Custom Identify protocol: `/introvert/id/1.0.0`
- Client-only mode for mobile nodes (no DHT storage)
- Server mode only for RBNs and Anchor nodes
- **Result:** Network invisible to standard IPFS crawlers

### Firewall Bypass

- Port 443 (HTTPS) for all traffic
- QUIC UDP for low-latency transport
- WebSocket tunnel fallback for restrictive networks
- **Result:** Works on corporate networks, hotels, airports, censored regions

### Traffic Camouflage

- All traffic appears as HTTPS on port 443
- QUIC multiplexing prevents traffic analysis
- No distinctive packet signatures
- **Result:** Deep Packet Inspection cannot distinguish from web browsing

### Threat Model

| Threat | Protection |
|--------|-----------|
| Central server compromise | No central servers exist |
| Metadata analysis | Dark mesh isolation |
| Man-in-the-middle | Noise IK static-static auth |
| Replay attacks | Timestamp validation + session caching |
| Handle impersonation | PoW + witness consensus |
| Storage theft | SQLCipher encryption at rest |
| Traffic analysis | Port 443 + QUIC multiplexing |

